input: Anne is kind. Anne is not nice. Anne is not round. Charlie is white. Erin is cold. Erin is kind. Erin is nice. Erin is quiet. Erin is not white. Gary is not cold. Gary is not kind. Gary is nice. Gary is not round. Gary is not white. If Gary is quiet then Gary is red. If something is quiet and kind then it is round. All white, quiet things are kind. White things are red. If something is red then it is quiet. If something is round and cold then it is nice. If something is round and not kind then it is not cold. If something is quiet then it is cold. Question: Charlie is nice.?
output:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Anne : obj
constant Charlie : obj
constant Erin : obj
constant Gary : obj

constant Kind : obj → Prop
constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop
constant White : obj → Prop
constant Cold : obj → Prop
constant Quiet : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Kind Anne
axiom T2 : ¬ Nice Anne
axiom T3 : ¬ Round Anne
axiom T4 : White Charlie
axiom T5 : Cold Erin
axiom T6 : Kind Erin
axiom T7 : Nice Erin
axiom T8 : Quiet Erin
axiom T9 : ¬ White Erin
axiom T10 : ¬ Cold Gary
axiom T11 : ¬ Kind Gary
axiom T12 : Nice Gary
axiom T13 : ¬ Round Gary
axiom T14 : ¬ White Gary

axiom R1 : Quiet Gary → Red Gary
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x ∧ Kind x → Round x
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, White x ∧ Quiet x → Kind x
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, White x → Red x
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Red x → Quiet x
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Round x ∧ Cold x → Nice x
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Round x ∧ ¬ Kind x → ¬ Cold x
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x → Cold x

theorem charlie_is_nice : Nice Charlie :=
begin
  apply R6,
  split,
  apply R2,
  split,
  apply R3,
  split,
  exact T4,
  apply R5,
  apply R4,
  exact T4,
  apply R8,
  apply R5,
  apply R4,
  exact T4,
end

-- The answer is True
